captions.text: - My confidence level is not that high,
but I hope to learn a lot today.

- Percussion isn't really
my thing musically.
- I'm willing to put good money
that I'm pretty horrific at it.
- I'm not in I.T., I'm here for diversity.
- First thing to do is always make sure

so I let Francis just
kind of, off the back,
- ♫ La la la la la la la
♫ La la la la la la ♫
- Put your own spin on things.
- Making the letter "P" with your lips,
or the letter "B" with your lips,
and forcing air out your lips,

really fast, tightening
this muscle and this muscle.
Will give your kick drum sound.

Adding those two sounds
together will give you:

With beatboxing, it is
the art of breath control.

So every now and then you're
gonna have to breathe,
but where do you do that?
Using the "K" sound as a device,

will give you the
opportunity to create sound,
and breathe at the same time.
- It's like, going through my nose!
- Yeah I know, I'm trying not to.

I get it now!
- [Joshua] Okay, you get it?

but more importantly put
your own spin on things.
and your sound is unlike anybody
Whatever it is, be yourself, be you,
and just have a good time,

making fart noises with you
lips, tongue, and cheek.

I've never done speed
before, but I feel like...
everything is going awesome right now.
